11_animate_transforms


  1. Question

    In Desmos, define function \(f\) with the equation below. \[f(x)~=~x^3-x\]

    Then, define the following four functions, and make a slider for \(t\): \[g(x)=f(x+t)\] \[h(x)=f(x)+t\] \[m(x)=f(tx)\] \[n(x)=t\cdot f(x)\]

    When slider \(t\) is animated, with domain (-10,10), those four functions will exhibit the four different behaviors shown below. Match the animations below to the four functions.

    Animation 1


    • Animation 1 matches

    Animation 2


    • Animation 2 matches

    Animation 3


    • Animation 3 matches

    Animation 4


    • Animation 4 matches


    Solution

    Id recommend actually using Desmos as described. It should show you the answers.

    • Animation 1 matches g(x) = f(x+t)
    • Animation 2 matches m(x) = f(tx)
    • Animation 3 matches n(x) = t*f(x)
    • Animation 4 matches h(x) = f(x)+t
